Marion 'Suge' Knight was chained down to a chair and wheeled into a California courtroom on Wednesday . 
  Death Row Records co-founder fell at a previous hearing while addressing murder charges levied against him . 
  Knight complained to Judge Ronald Coen and said he could walk . 
  The 49-year-old diabetic with a blood clot fell and hit his head at the previous bail hearing . 
  His lawyer said the chains and wheelchair were part of a 'ploy' to 'humiliate' his client . 
 